  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Emoji displayed in message box when request/send commands used in group chats for username having emoji short code. No need to decode any text in username in message box if it has emoji short codes (e.g. of such usernames: `ETH :smile:`, `:ok:`, `:s: :t: :a: :t: :u: :s:`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nOriginal username displays in message box when request/send commands used in group chats for username having emoji short code\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nEmoji displayed in message box when request/send commands used in group chats for username having emoji short code\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create user on DeviceA\r\n- Open Status and create user on DeviceB\r\n- DeviceA sets contact name having emoji short codes (e.g. `S:t:a:t:u:s :smile:`)\r\n- ContactA adds ContactB in contacts\r\n- ContactB creates group chat with ContactA\r\n- ContactB in group chat taps on /request and choose ContactA from the list\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nStatus version: Develop (9f9155, 0.9.11d629), Release 0.9.13\r\nOperating System: Android 7.0, Android 6.0, iOS (11.2.2)\r\n\r\nTF session: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/7636858/sessions/13/?accessToken=mcnkONOYyYux0Mh1DdNtnZPIAbc",
